## Recommended Libraries

- **Zigzag/Swings**: Custom functions with scipy.signal.argrelextrema or implement peak/valley filtering (simple, no heavy deps). [stackoverflow](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/62454181/zigzag-indicator-in-python)
- **Fibonacci**: Manual calculations on swing points (retracements: 23.6%, 38.2%, 61.8%; extensions: 127.2%, 161.8%) or ta-py/stock-indicators. [eodhd](https://eodhd.com/financial-academy/technical-analysis-examples/fibonacci-sequence-in-trading-with-python)
- **Elliott Waves**: taew (PyPI) for labeling impulses/corrections with Fib validation; supplement with ElliottWaves or Elliott_System GitHub repos for pattern detection. [pypi](https://pypi.org/project/taew/)
- **Core TA/Processing**: Pandas for OHLCV, TA-Lib for basics; run offline in GitHub Actions to precompute annotations as JSON/CSV. [ta-lib.github](https://ta-lib.github.io/ta-lib-python/)
- **Viz/Frontend**: pytvchart or louisnw01/lightweight-charts-python to generate charts with candlesticks, zigzag lines, Fib lines, and wave labels. [github](https://github.com/filipemarques87/tradingview-chart-py)

## Best Implementation Strategy

Process CSV data in Python: Apply zigzag to find swings, compute Fib levels between points, then use taew-like rules to label potential waves (e.g., check Fib ratios for wave 2/4 retracements, wave 3/5 extensions). [elliottwave-forecast](https://elliottwave-forecast.com/elliottwave/importance-of-an-elliott-wave-zigzag-fibonacci-extension/)

Output JSON with time/value points for candlesticks, zigzag lines, Fib horizontals, and markers/labels for waves.

Serve via web: Backend (Flask/FastAPI) uploads CSVs, computes, sends JSON to JS frontend using Lightweight Charts API for custom series (LineSeries for zigzag/Fib, add labels). [tradingview](https://www.tradingview.com/charting-library-docs/latest/custom_studies/)

GitHub Actions: YAML workflow for lint/test/process sample CSVs on push/PR; deploy to Vercel/Netlify for static host or Render for Python app. [realpython](https://realpython.com/github-actions-python/)

